    "excerpt": "This weekday Amidah was offered by Miriam Rubin as an exercise during the Davvening Leadership Training Initiative (Week 3). She writes, \"I began writing this July of 2024 when I was still pregnant and finished it in February of 2025 when my daughter was about 4 months old.\" . . .",
    "content": "<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Source (English)</th>\n<th style=\"text-align: right;\">Source (Hebrew)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI stand upright,<br />\nheart over my womb,<br />\nfacing the east.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI inhale this precious breath,<br />\nthe air now inhabiting<br />\nthe house of my soul,<br />\nand exhale a call with my voice.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI ask permission to be here,<br />\nto offer prayers here.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nMay my lips open<br />\nand my voice exclaim a song<br />\nthat brings pleasure and nourishment<br />\nto <span class=\"divine-referent\">the source of life</span>.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nאֲדֹנָי שְׂפָתַי תִּפְתָּח<br />\nוּפִי יַגִּיד תְּהִלָּתֶֽךָ׃ <span class=\"citation\">(תהלים נא:יז)</span>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">1. Ancestors (Avot / Imahot)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nאָבוֹת וְאִמָּהוֹת\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nAncestors and Guides,<br />\nI invoke your love,<br />\ncare,<br />\nblessing,<br />\nprotection,<br />\nguidance,<br />\nand support.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nMagen Avraham<br />\nv’Ezrat Sarah.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nמָגֵן אַבְרָהָם<br />\nוְעֶזְרַת שָׂרָה׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">2. Source Of Miracles (Gevurot)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nגְּבוּרוֹת\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">Source of Life</span>,<br />\nI invoke and praise you,<br />\nthe force capable of creating<br />\nmiracles in my life.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nM&#8217;ḥayei Ha-Metim.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nמְחַיֵּה הַמֵּתִים׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">3. Source Of Holiness (Ḳadosh)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nקָדוֹשׁ\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">Source of loving evolution</span>,<br />\nI invoke you to correct any imbalances<br />\nor impurities within my field,<br />\nso that I may be presentable,<br />\nand able to be present in this <span class=\"divine-referent\">Holy Space</span>.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nHa-El HaḲadosh.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nהָאֵל הַקָּדוֹשׁ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">4. Humble Knowing (Ḥonen HaDa&#8217;at)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nחוֹנֵן הַדָּעַת\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI allow my attention to rest in the place<br />\nwhere inner knowing, insight, and understanding<br />\nbubble forth within me.<br />\nI offer praise to the source of life,<br />\nand I allow the divine to communicate with me<br />\nand for awareness to grow within me.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nḤonen HaDa&#8217;at.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nחוֹנֵן הַדָּעַת׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">5. Repentance (Teshuvah)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nתְּשׁוּבָה\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI stand before<br />\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">the presence<br />\nof compassion,<br />\nunderstanding,<br />\nforgiveness<br />\nand right action</span><br />\nto ask to re-align my life<br />\nwith joy,<br />\nhappiness,<br />\nvitality,<br />\nsuccess<br />\nand fulfillment.<br />\nI align my being<br />\nwith the vision and manifestation<br />\nof my most fulfilled life.<br />\nI allow myself to notice<br />\nwhat falls out of alignment,<br />\nand to invoke compassion,<br />\nunderstanding,<br />\nforgiveness<br />\nand right action.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nHa-Rotseh ḆiTshuvah.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nהָרוֹצֶה בִתְשׁוּבָה׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">6. Forgiveness (Seliḥah)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nסְלִיחָה\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI invoke the divine power of forgiveness<br />\nand ask the source of life to help me<br />\nin forgiving myself and others<br />\nfor any transgression and hurt.<br />\nI ask for forgiveness,<br />\nand ask to be forgiven.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nḤanun HaMarbeh Lislōaḥ.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nחַנּוּן הַמַּרְבֶּה לִסְלֹחַ׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">7. A Redeemed World (Gəulah)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nגְּאֻלָּה\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI invoke the presence of Geulah,<br />\nand ask this presence to fill the world<br />\nand bring healing,<br />\ncompassion,<br />\nand evolution.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span><br />\nGōel Yisrael.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nגּוֹאֵל יִשְׂרָאֵל׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">8. Bring Healing to those who are ill (Refuah)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nרְפוּעָה\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI invoke the presence of <span class=\"divine-referent\">Hashem Refuah</span>, the great healer,<br />\nand ask that this presence come<br />\nand heal those who are sick —<br />\n(specifically . . .) —<br />\nMay they be healed<br />\nand blossom with health and vitality.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nRofeh Ḥolei Amo Yisrael.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nרוֹפֵא חוֹלֵא עָמוֹ יִשְׂרָאֵל׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">9. We Ask for a Year of Blessing (M’varekh HaShanim)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nמְבָרֵךְ הַשָּׁנִים\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI have complete trust<br />\nwith perfect faith and gratitude<br />\nthat this year ahead<br />\nis filled with joy,<br />\nprosperity,<br />\nsuccess,<br />\nhealth,<br />\nhappiness,<br />\ngenerosity,<br />\nsecurity,<br />\npeace,<br />\nand miracles!<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nM’varekh HaShanim.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nמְבָרֵךְ הַשָּׁנִים׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">10. End Of Exile (Ḳibbuts Galuyot)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nקִבּוּץ גָּלוּיוֹת\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI invoke the mother who calls her children home.<br />\nMay the human heart<br />\nhear her call like a Shofar<br />\nand repent our ways,<br />\nand create an Eden once again.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nM’kabets Nidḥei Amo Yisrael.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nמְקַבֵּץ נִדְחֵי עַמּוֹ יִשְׂרָאֵל׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">11. Justice (Tsedeḳ)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nצֶדֶק\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI invoke the spirit of righteousness,<br />\njustice,<br />\nand compassion<br />\nto fill the hearts and minds of all man.<br />\nFill our world, fill our actions,<br />\nfill me, fill my actions.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nMelekh Ohev Tsedaḳah u’Mishpat.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nמֶלֶךְ אוֹהֵב צְדָקָה וּמִשְׁפָּט׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">12. Pray for the Failure of Evil Forces (Birkat Haminim)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבִּרְכַּת הַמִּינִים\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI pray for the heart of humanity.<br />\nI uplift the heart of the world.<br />\nI sing to you.<br />\nMay the forces of goodness prevail<br />\nand be much stronger than any force of evil!<br />\nMay the plans of evil be disrupted.<br />\nMay those creating disharmony<br />\nrepent immediately<br />\nand work towards the good of all.<br />\nMay the web of life be restored to harmony.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nShover Oyvim<br />\nu-Makhniya Zedim.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nשׁוֹבֵר אוֹיְבִים<br />\nוּמַכְנִיעַ זֵדִים׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">13. Pray for the Ascended Masters (Tsadiḳim)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nצַדִּיקִים\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nI invoke the righteous<br />\nand evolutionary strength<br />\nof the Tsadiḳim.<br />\nPlease bestow blessings of prosperity and success<br />\nfor those who are building a sacred world of peace.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nMish&#8217;an u-Mivtaḥ LaTsadiḳim.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nמִשְׁעָן וּמִבְטָח לַצַּדִּיקִים׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">14. Build A City Of Peace (Binyan Yerushalyim)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבִּנְיַן יְרוּשָׁלַיִם\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">Great Spirit</span>,<br />\nassemble us,<br />\nfill us with the knowledge of peace,<br />\nwisdom,<br />\nand beauty.<br />\nMay we join hearts and minds<br />\nto build dwelling places of peace.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nBoneh Yerushalayim.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nבּוֹנֵה יְרוּשָׁלָיִם׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">15. Wellspring of Salvation (Malkhut Beit David)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nמַלְכוּת בֵּית דָּוִד\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nPlease <span class=\"divine-referent\">God</span>,<br />\ncause salvation to spring up<br />\nand flourish in our world.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nMatsmiaḥ Ḳeren Yeshua.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nמַצְמִיחַ קֶרֶן יְשׁוּעָה׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">16. (Ḳabbalat T’filah)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nקַבָּלַת תְּפִלָּה\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">Spirit of Life</span>,<br />\nI love you.<br />\nPlease receive nourishment<br />\nthrough these words.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nShome&#8217;a T’filah.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nשׁוֹמֵעַ תְּפִלָּה׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">17. (Shekhinah)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nשְׁכִינָה\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">Great Shekhinah</span>,<br />\nmay you be united again with your world<br />\nthat you love so much.<br />\nMay you be forever honored,<br />\nrespected,<br />\nand welcomed home.<br />\nWe crown you as Queen of the world once more.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nHaMaḥzir Shekhinato L’Tsiōn.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nהַמַּחֲזִיר שְׁכִינָתוֹ לְצִיּוֹן׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">18. Gratitude (Modim)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nמוֹדִים\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\nThank you ancestors, guides,<br />\nthank you <span class=\"divine-referent\">Hashem</span>,<br />\nthank you, <span class=\"divine-referent\">Goodness</span><br />\nfor the pleasure of connecting with you.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nHaTov Shimkha<br />\nu-lekha naeh ləhodot.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nהַטּוֹב שִׁמְךָ<br />\nוּלְךָ נָאֶה לְהוֹדוֹת׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 10px; text-decoration-thickness: from-font;\">19. (Shalom)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nשָׁלוֹם\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<span class=\"divine-referent\">Great Spirit</span>,<br />\nbring your peace,<br />\nto all the nations of the world,<br />\nand to the nation of Yisrael.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nBarukh Atah <span class=\"divine-referent\">Adonai</span>,<br />\nHamvorekh et Amo Yisrael BaShalom.\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה יְיָ<br />\nהַמְבָרֵךְ אֶת עַמּוֹ יִשְׂרָאֵל בַּשָּׁלוֹם׃\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr />\n<p>This weekday Amidah was offered by Miriam Rubin as an exercise during the Davvening Leadership Training Initiative (Week 3). She writes, &#8220;I began writing this July of 2024 when I was still pregnant and finished it in February of 2025 when my daughter was about 4 months old.&#8221; This form of Amidah can also be found in Seder Ḥibbur Berakhot, the earliest example of Italian liturgy. For comparison, find Reb Zalman&#8217;s <a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/?p=30340\">alternative Amidah</a> and <a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/?p=21107\">Affirmations</a>.<br />\n <br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n",
